<hr class="post-separator" aria-hidden="true" />
<article id="post-36989" class="post-36989 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news">
			<header class="entry-header">
			<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="https://library.ryerson.ca/blog/2020/09/ryerson-reads-they-said-this-would-be-fun-by-eternity-martis/">Ryerson Reads: They Said This Would Be Fun by Eternity Martis</a></h1>
		</header><!-- .entry-header -->
	
	<div class="entry-content">

				<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="sep">Posted on </span><a href="https://library.ryerson.ca/blog/2020/09/ryerson-reads-they-said-this-would-be-fun-by-eternity-martis/" title="11:25 am" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2020-09-16T11:25:58-04:00" pubdate>September 16, 2020</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="https://library.ryerson.ca/blog/author/jenna-charlton/" title="View all posts by Ryerson Library" rel="author">Ryerson Library</a></span></span>		</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
		
		
<p>Ryerson Reads is an annual campus-wide reading program for all Ryerson’s students, faculty, and staff. This year, in collaboration with <a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/sexual-violence/">Consent Comes First</a>, the Office of Sexual Violence Support and Education, Ryerson Reads will be reading <em>They Said This Would Be Fun</em> by Ryerson Alumni, Eternity Martis.</p>



<p>This engaging book is about being a Black student on a predominantly white campus dealing with misogynoir and other forms of anti-Black racism. A book-smart kid from Toronto, Eternity  was excited to move away to Western University for her undergraduate degree. But as one of the few Black students there, she soon discovered that the campus experiences she’d seen in movies were far more complex in reality.</p>



<p><a href="https://library.ryerson.ca/ryerson-reads/" data-type="URL" data-id="https://library.ryerson.ca/ryerson-reads/">Register now </a>to receive a free copy or the book (print or ebook) and learn more about the program! </p>
		
		
		<footer class="entry-meta">
			<span>This entry was posted in <a href="https://library.ryerson.ca/blog/category/news/" rel="category tag">News</a> by <a href="https://library.ryerson.ca/blog/author/jenna-charlton/">Ryerson Library</a>. Bookmark the <a href="https://library.ryerson.ca/blog/2020/09/ryerson-reads-they-said-this-would-be-fun-by-eternity-martis/" title="Permalink to Ryerson Reads: They Said This Would Be Fun by Eternity Martis" rel="bookmark">permalink</a>.</span>					</footer><!-- .entry-meta -->

