<hr class="post-separator" aria-hidden="true" />
<article id="post-36813" class="post-36813 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-news">
			<header class="entry-header">
			<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="https://library.ryerson.ca/blog/2020/09/ryerson-celebrates-indigenous-identity-with-artwork-installation/">Ryerson celebrates Indigenous identity with artwork installation</a></h1>
		</header><!-- .entry-header -->
	
	<div class="entry-content">

				<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="sep">Posted on </span><a href="https://library.ryerson.ca/blog/2020/09/ryerson-celebrates-indigenous-identity-with-artwork-installation/" title="2:44 pm" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2020-09-02T14:44:52-04:00" pubdate>September 2, 2020</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="https://library.ryerson.ca/blog/author/jenna-charlton/" title="View all posts by Ryerson Library" rel="author">Ryerson Library</a></span></span>		</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
		
		
<p></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" width="650" height="434" src="https://library.ryerson.ca/wp-content/uploads/Image-22-650x434.jpg" alt class="wp-image-36817 jetpack-lazy-image" data-lazy-srcset="https://library.ryerson.ca/wp-content/uploads/Image-22-650x434.jpg 650w, https://library.ryerson.ca/wp-content/uploads/Image-22-300x200.jpg 300w, https://library.ryerson.ca/wp-content/uploads/Image-22-150x100.jpg 150w, https://library.ryerson.ca/wp-content/uploads/Image-22-768x513.jpg 768w, https://library.ryerson.ca/wp-content/uploads/Image-22-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://library.ryerson.ca/wp-content/uploads/Image-22-2048x1367.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" data-lazy-src="https://library.ryerson.ca/wp-content/uploads/Image-22-650x434.jpg?is-pending-load=1" srcset="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7"><noscript><img loading="lazy" width="650" height="434" src="https://library.ryerson.ca/wp-content/uploads/Image-22-650x434.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-36817" srcset="https://library.ryerson.ca/wp-content/uploads/Image-22-650x434.jpg 650w, https://library.ryerson.ca/wp-content/uploads/Image-22-300x200.jpg 300w, https://library.ryerson.ca/wp-content/uploads/Image-22-150x100.jpg 150w, https://library.ryerson.ca/wp-content/uploads/Image-22-768x513.jpg 768w, https://library.ryerson.ca/wp-content/uploads/Image-22-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://library.ryerson.ca/wp-content/uploads/Image-22-2048x1367.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" /></noscript></figure>



<p>Photography by rising star Nadya Kwandibens is on display at the Ryerson Library west entrance.</p>



<p>The <a href="https://library.ryerson.ca/">Ryerson University Library</a> has unveiled a large-scale public artwork by photographer <a href="https://www.redworks.ca/">Nadya Kwandibens, external link</a> to commemorate the university’s engagement with the annual <a href="https://www.naisa.org/">Native American Indigenous Studies Association (NAISA), external link</a> conference. The 10 x 15.7-foot portrait is on display over the west entrance to the Library as part of the university’s commitment to increase Indigenous visibility and celebration on campus, to educate the community about Indigenous issues and to inspire meaningful conversations.</p>



<p>Captured in 2010, the portrait is part of Kwandibens’ Concrete Indians series, which reflects on contemporary Indigenous identity. Collaborating with subjects who volunteer their participation, she explores what urbanization means for Indigenous peoples across Turtle Island and how living in urban areas can affect one’s cultural identity.</p>



<p><a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/news-events/news/2020/09/ryerson-celebrates-indigenous-identity-with-artwork-installation/?utm_source=Ryerson+Today+Contacts&amp;utm_campaign=2f67621a2f-20200902&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_term=0_4843a7a799-2f67621a2f-89300631" data-type="URL" data-id="https://www.ryerson.ca/news-events/news/2020/09/ryerson-celebrates-indigenous-identity-with-artwork-installation/?utm_source=Ryerson+Today+Contacts&amp;utm_campaign=2f67621a2f-20200902&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_term=0_4843a7a799-2f67621a2f-89300631">Read the full press release in Ryerson Today</a></p>



<p></p>
		
		
